SLS 26RS-61 ORIGINAL
2026 Regular Session
SENATE CONCURRENT RESOLUTION NO. 47
BY SENATOR SEABAUGH
COMMENDATIONS. Commends Joe Horn on being inducted into the 2026 class of the
Louisiana Sports Hall of Fame.
1 A CONCURRENT RESOLUTION
2 To commend Joe Horn on being inducted into the 2026 class of the Louisiana Sports Hall
3 of Fame.
4 WHEREAS, each year the Louisiana Sports Hall of Fame in Natchitoches, Louisiana
5 collaborates with the Louisiana Sports Writers Association in selecting a limited number of
6 sports figures who embody the character, skill, talent, and accomplishment worthy of being
7 named to the Hall of Fame; and
8 WHEREAS, the 2026 Louisiana Sports Hall of Fame Induction Class includes Joe
9 Horn; and
10 WHEREAS, Joe Horn, a dynamic and electrifying wide receiver, earned the
11 admiration of fans and teammates alike through his remarkable playmaking ability,
12 leadership, and passion for the game of football; and
13 WHEREAS, born in New Haven, Connecticut, on January 16, 1972, Horn rose to
14 prominence in the National Football League and established himself as one of the most
15 productive wide receivers in the history of the New Orleans Saints franchise; and
16 WHEREAS, Horn joined the Saints in 2000 as an unrestricted free agent after
17 beginning his professional career with the Kansas City Chiefs and immediately made an
18 impact, helping lead the Saints to the NFC West Division title and a playoff appearance in
