1 his first season with the team; and
2 WHEREAS, during his seven seasons in New Orleans from 2000 through 2006, Horn
3 compiled an extraordinary 523 receptions for 7,622 receiving yards and 50 touchdowns,
4 placing him among the most accomplished receivers in franchise history; and
5 WHEREAS, Horn's fifty touchdown receptions broke the previous team record and
6 helped establish him as one of the premier scoring threats in Saints history; and
7 WHEREAS, Horn set a franchise record with eleven touchdown receptions during
8 the 2004 season and delivered one of the most memorable single-game performances in
9 Saints history when he recorded four touchdown receptions against the New York Giants on
10 December 21, 2004; and
11 WHEREAS, during his tenure with the Saints, Horn recorded 28 one-hundred yard
12 receiving games, a team record at the time, and set a franchise single-season record with 94
13 receptions and 1,399 receiving yards in 2004; and
14 WHEREAS, from 2000 through 2002, Horn enjoyed one of the most productive
15 stretches by a wide receiver in franchise history, averaging 88 receptions, 1,306 receiving
16 yards, and eight touchdowns per season while earning selections to the Pro Bowl in each of
17 those three seasons, as well as again in 2004; and
18 WHEREAS, Horn concluded a distinguished twelve-year NFL career with 603
19 receptions, 8,744 receiving yards, and 58 touchdowns while also spending time with the
20 Atlanta Falcons; and
21 WHEREAS, in recognition of his exceptional impact on the franchise and his
22 beloved status among Saints fans, Horn was inducted into the New Orleans Saints Hall of
23 Fame in 2010 during his first year of eligibility; and
24 WHEREAS, Horn's legacy continues in the next generation, as his son, Jaycee Horn,
25 was selected in the first round of the 2021 NFL Draft by the Carolina Panthers and has
26 emerged as one of the league's promising defensive backs; and
27 WHEREAS, through his outstanding athletic achievements, charismatic personality,
28 and dedication to the game of football, Joe Horn has left a lasting legacy with the New
29 Orleans Saints and has brought pride and excitement to the fans of Louisiana.
30 THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED that the Legislature of Louisiana does hereby
